                            <comment id="14304290" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2015 23:20:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1656949 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1656949&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1656949&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2281&quot; title=&quot;Yellow box shown&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2281&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2281&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: respect (some) annotation flags&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14304310" author="tilman" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2015 23:33:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2281&quot; title=&quot;Yellow box shown&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2281&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2281&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-2_unc.pdf is a reduced and uncompressed version of that file. The annotation is at 23 0 obj.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve inserted that the annotation isn&apos;t rendered if the flags &quot;invisible&quot;, &quot;hidden&quot; or &quot;noview&quot; are set. However this isn&apos;t perfect. There are flags that allow an annotation to be printed, but not viewed. But at this time PageDrawer doesn&apos;t know whether it is viewing or printing. (And what is &quot;rendering in an image&quot;? Does this count as &quot;viewing&quot;?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14304323" author="jahewson" created="Tue, 3 Feb 2015 23:43:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Graphics2D provides this information via getDeviceConfiguration().getDevice().getType(), which is TYPE_PRINTER when the device is a printer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14305153" author="jira-bot" created="Wed, 4 Feb 2015 14:28:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1657251 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1657251&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1657251&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2281&quot; title=&quot;Yellow box shown&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2281&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2281&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: improve respecting (some) annotation flags, drop support of invisible flag&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14305170" author="tilman" created="Wed, 4 Feb 2015 14:38:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; thanks for the hint.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d dropped the support for the &quot;Invisible&quot; flag because 1) it wasn&apos;t the problem here 2) I haven&apos;t understood the spec, this can be done in a new issue if we come up with a test file. But I have improved printer and screen related options.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14305175" author="tilman" created="Wed, 4 Feb 2015 14:39:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2281&quot; title=&quot;Yellow box shown&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2281&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2281&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-yellownoprint.pdf has the yellow box with the noprint flag. It shows up in the viewer, but not when printing from the PDFReader application.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14305177" author="tilman" created="Wed, 4 Feb 2015 14:42:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Setting to resolved. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ssteiner1&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ssteiner1&quot;&gt;ssteiner1&lt;/a&gt; thanks for the sample file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14305198" author="msahyoun" created="Wed, 4 Feb 2015 15:02:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A quick explanation on &apos;Invisible&apos; annotations. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The PDF specification describes several standard annotations but the list of annotations is extensible i.e. one could define new annotation types. The handling of annotations should be done by an annotation handler and is implementation specific. This allows to extend the list of annotation types.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the spec for &apos;invisible&apos;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If set, do not display the annotation if it does not belong to one of the standard annotation types and no annotation handler is available. If clear, display such an unknown annotation using an appearance stream specified by its appearance dictionary&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For PDFBox and rendering IMHO&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if &apos;invisible&apos; is SET&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;render using the appearance stream&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if there is none and it&apos;s a standard annotation generate an appearance stream with defaults and render that&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if it&apos;s not one of the standard annotations don&apos;t render it&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;maybe provide a mechanism to provide appearance generation for non standard appearances&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;if &apos;invisible&apos; is CLEAR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;render using the appearance stream&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;But I think we can very much wait until such a document comes up.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
